text:
This vector served as additional level 0 entry vector for CDS parts.

pICH41308-mrfp1-/\lacO Level 0 vector containing a mRFP1DlacO cassette (no inducer, such as IPTG, needed), with BsaI and SapI recognition sites. Upon successful cloning in the future, the mRFP1ΔlacO cassette would be replaced by the target insert, resulting in white clones on the plate, while clones carrying the parent vector still show red colourization.

The system states that the plasmid is not RFC1000 compatible, however this is due to the fact that its annotated as an entry vector, which requires two SapI restriction sites to insert parts into the vector.&#x20;

This vector served as additional level 1 entry vector for the RFC1000 framework.

MoClo Level 1 vector with a pICH47742 backbone (AmpR) and a *mRFP1*Δ*lac*O cassette (red fluorescent protein cassette lacking *lac*O, deleted via QuikChange(R) mutagenesis, therefore no inducer is needed).&#x20;

The system states that the plasmid is not RFC1000 compatible, however this is due to the fact that its annotated as an entry vector, which requires two SapI restriction sites to insert parts into the vector.&#x20;

This pBSMuL1-like MoClo level 1 vector (only containing *ori E. coli*, *repB*, *amp*R, *kan*R, *mRFP1*Δ*lac*O cassette) can be used to assemble transcription units in the RFC1000 framework for a multi-copy overexpression strategy in B. subtilis.

pBSMuL1 is a *E. coli* – *B. subtilis* shuttle vector for protein overproduction harbouring *amp*R, *kan*R, and BsaI recognition sites with an additional *mRFP1*ΔlacO cassette (see pBS2EΔ*lac*O; no need for inducers, such as IPTG, red colourization of *E. coli* cells harbouring this vector).

The system states that the plasmid is not RFC1000 compatible, however this is due to the fact that its annotated as an entry vector, which requires two SapI restriction sites to insert parts into the vector.&#x20;
